                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11540.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to certain
                            <gloss type="to">American diplomatic missions</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="12" xml:id="d695fn12">Sent to the Embassies at Mexico City, London,
                        Paris, Vienna, Berlin, Rome, Madrid, and Tokyo, and the Legation at
                        Guatemala.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-18T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following statement was given out from the White House at noon today: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>General Huerta is still insisting upon doing something less than has been
                            demanded and something less than would constitute an acknowledgment that
                            his representatives were entirely in the wrong in the indignities they
                            have put upon the Government of the United States. The President has
                            determined that if General Huerta has not yielded by six o’clock on
                            Sunday afternoon, he will take the matter to Congress on Monday.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
